Villagers want the road tarmacked to help alleviate their suffering and open market opportunities.Area residents said farmers are unable to ferry their output to the market due to the poor state of the road. Residents of Kamore in Naivasha, Nakuru County have petitioned the government to rehabilitate a crucial road in the far flung village which is currently impassable.
They held demonstrations on Saturday, accusing both the county and national governments of neglecting them for years.
Peter Kaara, a resident and former senior chief, said the road was gravelled during the administration of the first President Jomo Kenyatta.    



