They called for the tarmacking of the road to help alleviate their sufferings and open up market opportunities.
The villagers, at the same time, called on the government to intervene in a land row involving a private developer accused of having grabbed a five-acre farm set aside for a nursery school.
A resident, Mariah Njenga, who has resided in the area for the past 50 years, expressed dismay after a nursery school was torched by unknown assailants a week ago.

